# 3. Features Not Implemented 

The following items were identified as desirable improvements but not required by the assignment. These were not implemented due to the 20-hour cap:

### Frontend Styling / UX
- No responsive layout
- No CSS frameworks
- No page routing or multi-page layout
- No advanced error/success UI

### Account Management
- No password reset flow
- No email verification
- No profile page
- No logout timer or token refresh logic

### Article Enhancements
- No pagination or infinite scroll
- No article metadata extraction (title scraping)
- No editing of existing articles

### Security Hardening
- No rate limiting
- No CSRF protection (not needed for local dev)
- No environment-based config switching

### Deployment
- No Dockerfile
- No production bundling of frontend + backend
- Not deployed to any hosting platform (local-only as required)

